, "root": "zyn", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, MA, Msb, K,) aor."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yaziynuhu", "text_ar": "يَزِينُهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Msb,) inf. n."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "zayonN", "text_ar": "زَيْنٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (MA, Msb, KL, TA;) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "zy~nhu", "text_ar": "زيّنهُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, MA, Msb, K,) inf. n."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "tazoyiynN", "text_ar": "تَزْيِينٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (Msb, KL, TA;) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^azaAnahu", "text_ar": "اَزَانَهُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Msb, K,) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^azoyanahu", "text_ar": "اَزْيَنَهُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (K,) which is its original form, (TA,) inf. n."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_izaAnapN", "text_ar": "اـِزَانَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (Msb;) signify the same; (S, MA, Msb, K;)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "it, adorned, ornamented, decorated, decked, bedecked, garnished, embellished, beautified,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "graced, him,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "it."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(MA, KL, PS: [and the like is indicated in the S and Msb and K.]) ["}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "zaAnahu", "text_ar": "زَانَهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "said of a quality, and of an action, and of a saying, is best rendered"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "It adorned him,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "graced him,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "was an honour to him; contr. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$aAnahu", "text_ar": "شَانَهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; as is indicated in the S and K: and sometimes means"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "it was his pride:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "zy~nhu", "text_ar": "زيّنهُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "means as expl. above: and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "he embellished it, dressed it up,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "trimmed it;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "said in this sense as relating to language: and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "he embellished it,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "dressed it up,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "namely, an action &c. to another ("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ligayorihi", "text_ar": "لِغَيْرِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "); often said in this sense of the Devil; (as in the Kur vi. 43, &c.;) i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "he commended it"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "to him:]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "zaAnahu ka*aA", "text_ar": "زَانَهُ كَذَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "zy~nhu", "text_ar": "زيّنهُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Such a thing adorned him,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c.,] are expl. as said when one's excellence ["}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faDoluhu", "text_ar": "فَضْلُهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", as I read for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fElh", "text_ar": "فعله"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", an evident mistranscription,] appears either by speech or by action: and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A@ll~`hi liloA^a$oyaA='i", "text_ar": "ا@للّٰهِ لِلْاَشْيَا=ءِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "tazoyiynu", "text_ar": "تَزْيِينُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "God's adorning,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c.,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of things"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] is sometimes by means of his creating them"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "muzay~anap", "text_ar": "مُزَيَّنَة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[i. e. adorned, &c.]; and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Aln~aAsi", "text_ar": "النَّاسِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "tazoyiynu", "text_ar": "تَزْيِينُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The adorning,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c.,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of men"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "], by their abundance of property, and by their speech, i. e. by their extolling Him. (Er-Rághib, TA.) One says,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "zaAnahu AlHusonu", "text_ar": "زَانَهُ الحُسْنُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Beauty adorned,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "graced, him,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "it"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. And Mejnoon says,"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "fayaA rab~i A_i*o Say~arota layolaY liYa AlhawaY\n                      \n                     \n                        fazin~iY liEayonayohaA kamaA zinotahaA liyaA"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "And, O my Lord, since Thou hast made Leylà to be to me the object of love, then grace Thou me to her eyes like as Thou hast graced her to me"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (S, TA: but in the former,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mina AlhawY", "text_ar": "مِنَ الهَوى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in the place of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "liYa AlhawaY", "text_ar": "لِىَ الهَوَى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". [The reading in the S means"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of the objects of love:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "hawFY", "text_ar": "هَوًى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", being originally an inf. n., may be used alike as sing. and pl.])"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Als~iloEapi fiY AlbayoEi", "text_ar": "السِّلْعَةِ فِى البَيْعِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "tazoyiynu", "text_ar": "تَزْيِينُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[means"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The setting off,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "commending, of a commodity in selling;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and] is allowed, if without concealment of a fault, or defect, from the purchaser, and without lying in the attribution and description of the article. (TA.)"}], "source_refs": ["S", "MA", "Msb", "K", "TA"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}